result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Jorge Kenneth Cisneros was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Probation will be extended until fine is paid in full.

The defendant must obtain his GED.

The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
The defendant may not consume or possess alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns.
The defendant must submit a DNA sample with surcharge assessed.

The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

The defendant must attend at least two AA meeting per week and is to provide proof of attendance to his P&P agent.

The defendant is to attend and successfully complete an inpatient treatment program for alcohol, drug and dual diagnosis and follow thru with all recommendations.

The defendant must successfully complete any aftercare of AODA following his inpatient treatment.

Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros appears via telephone and in court is his attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. records.addlTxt: Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Also called 14CF108 and 15CF147. Called at 10:48. Counsel has received PSI's, no errors or ommissions on PSI's noted. Court has reviewed the PSI's. State - received information on credit - 14CF108 - 6 days credit, 14CF94 - 4 days credit, 15CF147 - 163 days applied pending on how the court rules for stated reasons - State makes argument prior to sentencing - recommends on 14CF94 - count #1 - 6 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of ES, - will make consecutive argument but concurent to each other; 14CF108 - count #4 - 5 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 2 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of ES - consecutive to 14CF94; on 15CF147 - #1 - 9 months - concurrent to 14CF108, count #2 - 90 days - concurrent to count #1, count #3 - 3.5 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 1.5 years of initial confinement followed by 2 years of ES, counts #5 and #6 - 6 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of ES - concurrent to each other but consecutive to 14CF94. Court clarifies State's sentence recommendations. Burns makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends 9-12 months of incarceration followed by probation (as PSI recommends). Defendant makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 14CF94 - 4 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 2 years of initial confinement followed by 2 years of ES; 14CF108 - 6 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of intial confinement followed by 3 of ES - stayed - place on probation for 3 years - consecutive to sentence on 14CF94; 15CF147 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years, consecutive to sentence on 14CF94, conditions of ES and probation:  AODA and follow thru, attend and successful complete a inpatient treatment program for alcohol, drug and dual diagnosis and follow thru with all recommendations and successfully complete any aftercare of AODA following his inpatient treatment, attend at least 2 AA meeting each week and submit proof of attendance to P&P agent, obtain GED, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns; fine on 14CF94 of $3000.00 plus costs - probation to be extended until fine is paid in full; credit on 14CF94 - 6 days; 14CF108 and 15CF147 - sentences are concurrent to each other but consecutive to 14CF94 - 167 days credit on 14CF108 and 15CF147 if revoked, revoke license for 3 years on 14CF94, IID on any vehicles titled in his name and DL for 3 years commencing upon issuance of a valid DL, costs on each count in other cases, submit DNA sample with expunction rights, no possession of firearms, no voting rights, not eligible for earned release programs, right to appeal, adjourned.

Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:07 AM. Called 14CF94, 15CF147 and 14CF108. State - resolved - defense will ask for PSI with both parties free to aruge and State has no objection to the request of the PSI, 14CF94 - plead G to count #1, dismiss #2; 14CF108 - plead to count #4 and remaining counts DRI - have complied with victim notification requirement with restitution of $66.00 owed to victim (without VW surcharge), 15CF147 - dismiss count #4, plead G to counts #1, #2, #3, #5 and #6. Burns agrees except for she thought that the State was bound by the recommendation of the PSI. State disagrees. Recess to talk to client (9:09 AM). Back on record at 9:12 AM. Burns has discussed the difference with her client and they are still willing to proceed today. Cisneros agrees. Court - 14CF108 - DRI counts #1, #2 and #3, Cisneros pleads G to count #4 as alleged; 15CF147 - court dismisses count #4, Cisneros pleads G to counts #1, #2, #3, #5 and #6 - all as alleged; 14CF94 - dismiss count #2 and Cisneros pleads G to count #1 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty. State does not object to PSI and asks that he be remanded to FOSO until sentencing. Burns requests PSI. Court makes statement in regards to request for PSI. Court will order a PSI, remands to FOSO, sets for sentencing hearing  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 12, 2016 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 3:10 PM. Called 14CF94, 14CF108, 15CF147. Burns has resolution on 2 cases and 15CF147 one of the counts they do not have an agreement on. Burns asks for adjournment to allow time to talk with DA. Off record, 3:12 PM. Back on the record, 3:15 PM. Court will adjourn. Bond continued.  Final pre-trial scheduled for March 9, 2016 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in custody.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:04 PM. Also called 14CF108 and 15CF147. State - believes 15CF147 will be a waiver of PH and the defendant will be pleading on 14CF94 and 14CF108. Burns and Cisneros agree. Court has waiver of PH form, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his right to PH, finds probable cause, binds over for trial. State has filed Information that mirrors the complaint. Burns has Information, waives reading of it, will proceed to ARGN and enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts pleas, continues bond and prior to setting for further proceedings, Court asks about the other cases. Burns states issues with going forward today with the plea on 14CF94 and 14CF108. Court understands. Court sets all matters for FPT. Court continues bond on all three matters.  Final pre-trial scheduled for February 17, 2016 at 02:15 pm.

Called at 4:05 a.m. Jorge Cisneros appears in person along with his attorney Mary Burns. State appears by Jodi Bednar-Clemens. Here for a motion hearing. State objects - calls for speculation - sustained (4:19 PM). State objects - calls for speculation - overruled (4:20 PM). State objects - mischaracterizes testimony - sustained (4:24 PM). State objects - relevance - sustained (4:26 PM). State objects - relevance - sustained (4:27 PM). Re-direct by State at 4:27 PM. Re-cross by Burns at 4:28 PM. Tanner excused at 4:28 PM. State makes final argument prior to ruling on motion - asks court to deny motion. Burns responds. State responds. Court makes ruling - denies motion for stated reasons. Court asks to set this matter for FPT on January for stated reaons. State has no objections - no negotitations were made until motion was heard. Burns does not have any objections to that. Cisneros has no objections to that condition. Court adds that condition to the bond as well. Burns will now waive time limits for PH.
